<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                            <head>Nationality of Children born of Alien Parents.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                            Office</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11
                                        1868</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The accompanying circular was sent from the foreign office to her
                                Majesty’s representatives at European courts:</p>
                            <p>“I have to instruct you to furnish me with a report for the
                                information of the Naturalization Commission on the state of
                                the——law with regard to the nationality of children born of alien
                                parents within the——dominions.”</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>